1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper uses statistical learning methods to analyze visual features of designs, which falls under the domain of computer vision.
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the relationship between social network position and novelty of designs, which falls under the domain of social and information networks.
3. cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) - Although the paper is primarily focused on visual design, it is possible that some of the statistical learning methods used could also be applied to sound and music computing.
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper touches on the success of designs, which could be related to user experience and human-computer interaction.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with visual designs shared on an online social network, which could be considered a form of multimedia.
